Muffin comes from the French word moufflet which means soft. With a preparation time of 10 minutes and a cooking time of 20 minutes, your fresh muffins will be ready within 30 minutes. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Preheat the oven to moderately hot (200 - 180) degrees, fan-forced. Step 2 Grease an 80 ml muffin pan with butter. Step 3 In a large bowl, mix in the flour, butter, milk, coconut, raspberries, eggs and mix with fingertips until everything has combined well. Step 4 Divide the mixture among the holes of the prepared pan, then sprinkle the shredded coconut. Step 5 Bake for 20 minutes. Once baked, slide in a toothpick at the centre, ensure it comes out clean. Step 6 Set aside in a rack to cool. Enjoy them with a glass of cold milk or juice with friends and family. 